After huge success with his productions "Blessed", "Hazed", "Hyped", his breathtaking collaboration with Leventina, "The Tempest" and his unmistakeable house remix of "Thinking About You" by Calvin Harris, EDX continues to incorporate different musical ideas to create unbridled magic. His unique productions and killer remixes in the likes of Kaskade, Sebastian Ingrosso, Dubfire, Funkagenda and Avicii, set EDX apart in the world of house music, establishing him as one of the hottest names on the scene and nothing short of spectacular. "Reckless Ardor" reflects EDX's mastery of chord progression. The chords filter down to blend with a pumping groove while haunting vocals and breathy Ah's float on top, exemplifying pure emotion. Stir your senses with another stellar release, injecting warmth into the winter season. Let yourself go with "Reckless Ardor" into a deep house escapade, a deep hypnotic mood. I decided to put out a song, spur of the moment, to celebrate the start of my Better Places Tour next week! From November 14 - December 16 I'll be touring all around the U.S. Grab your tickets at www.betterplacestour.com Around 2 years ago I was in Miami for WMC/Ultra week and I was at my hotel getting ready to go play a gig. I had been reading Keith Richards' memoir called "Life" and I really loved how much he talked about his musical influences throughout the book. One of those influences was Bo Diddley. After I had listened to a few of Diddley's songs, one song in particular had this moment that kept looping in my mind. I pulled out my laptop right before my show and created the first, really rough version of this remix...I really enjoyed making this and I am so happy to share it with you after so long!
